<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step12_AsyncStreams"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 12 - Async Streams">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step12ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 12: Async Streams (IAsyncEnumerable)"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">ASYNC STREAMS: Processing items one at a time as they become available.

Normal async: you call a method, wait for ALL the data, then process it.
Async streams: data arrives piece by piece, and you process EACH piece as it comes.

Think of it like:
- Task&lt;List&lt;Item&gt;&gt; = "Here are ALL the items" (you wait for everything)
- IAsyncEnumerable&lt;Item&gt; = "Here is one item... here is another... here is another..."
  (you process each one immediately)

Uses "await foreach" instead of regular "foreach".
Uses "yield return" inside the method (just like IEnumerable, but async).

Real-world examples: reading database rows one at a time, processing a live
data feed, reading a large file line by line, streaming API results.</TextBlock>

            <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
                <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                        Content="Stream sensor data (IAsyncEnumerable)"
                        Command="{Binding StreamDataCommand}"
                        IsEnabled="{Binding IsStreaming, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
                <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}" Margin="10,5,0,5"
                        Content="Stop" Background="#E63946"
                        Command="{Binding StreamDataCancelCommand}"
                        IsEnabled="{Binding IsStreaming}"/>
            </StackPanel>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="300"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
